reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments: Nice and moist like lip gloss. I have this in three colors.

reviews.headline: Very disappointed in these
reviews.comments: If these were $5 it would almost be too much for what you get.  Most of the cooler toned shades lead to some form of hot pink on my lips.  Plus, these are one of those products you put on and the color just keeps changing.  So you might think you have a soft pink, but within an hour, it is a hot pink.  At very first application you might think they feel nice.  BUT, these on top of being weird in how they wear on you, DRY OUT YOUR LIPS!!!!  I have tried 3 different shades.  And they all dried out my lip.  I LOVE MAC, but these are a huge miss for me.  There are so many similar products out there for way less that are much more comfortable and provide consistent color.

reviews.headline: I would buy this product again and again
reviews.comments: Excellent. The color is my perfect match. It's not sticky and it's not messy. It is everything and more. I will continue to buy this product.

reviews.headline: No color change at all
reviews.comments: I ordered serve and vibe based off all the reviews. Neither had any color change at all. Not moustirizing or long lasting either. They should give IQ tests before letting just anyone publicly post a review. And tired of all the reviews written by people who got it for free so were "incentivised" to make it sound good. That shouldn't be allowed. Can't trust reviews anymore.

reviews.headline: Must buy

reviews.headline: Perfect Color
reviews.comments: Love the smell, application, its moisturizing  and natural pink color. Perfect.

reviews.headline: So cute!
reviews.comments: I got the color "serve" i gad been looking for a bright coral type color to replace a lip product that i loved that is no longer made. I have been looking for a replacement for a couple years now, and finally found it!!! Feels so nice on the lips and leaves behind a little stain too

reviews.headline: Wanted to love, but just OK
reviews.comments:
I saw great reviews for this product and was really excited to receive it. I purchased the light purple color and was hoping for a cooler tint with a pink undertone, like I had seen in reviews. 

The scent was nice and vanilla-y, and went on smoothly. But the more product I applied, the more sickly pink it became. I honestly think all these pH-color-changing products are the same color for everyone. 

It also dried out my lips quite a bit and then the sickly pink color looked all patchy.

Would I recommend this product? Only if the person had hydrated lips and wanted a sheer pop of color. But honestly there are probably better products out there.

reviews.headline: In love
reviews.comments: This is the definition of a no-makeup make-look product! I hate wearing most makeup but like feeling put together and pretty so this product is amazing! The color is easily buildable and lightweight! I am obsessed!

reviews.headline: Obsessed
reviews.comments: 10/10, no notes. Keeper for sure.

reviews.headline: Awful taste and smell
reviews.comments: I purchased this lip balm because I wanted something I could wear daily for hydration with a touch of colour. While the colour is absolutely beautiful, I'm disappointed by the strong chemical taste and smell. It's so unpleasant that it makes me question the ingredients and whether I'm exposing my lips and body to something harmful. Sadly, I'll have to return it despite loving the shade.

reviews.headline: Not what I expected
reviews.comments: I'm returning this, it is not clear, it makes my lips very pink. But it feels great, just don't want any tint.

reviews.headline: Like it
reviews.comments: Looks lighter and less shine than tested in store! Smoothe and comfortable feel.

reviews.headline: I LOVE this lip balm!
reviews.comments: It glides on effortlessly and looks beautiful!

reviews.headline: Great lip balm
reviews.comments: I purchaed this in two colors. The pale pink and coral. I was a little disappointed that there wasn't much difference in the colors when applied. However, I do like that it keeps my lips moisturized and doesn't feel sticky.

reviews.headline: Great for darker lips
reviews.comments: I saw a post on IG and had to try for myself. My lips have gotten darker due to hookah etcâ€¦ but this works perfect and tones them more. Also feels very hydrating and is not heavy. Beautful dewy feel.

reviews.headline: Love love love
reviews.comments: Love this tinted lip balm; I have the color grapely admired, which is the perfect purple/pink tint. It also smells like Dr. Pepper, which is a bonus.

reviews.headline: Love love love
reviews.comments: This does exactly the same thing as the Prada lip balm but with a better smell and also lasts longer on your lips. I found myself reapplying the Prada often. This one is half the price and I would say is better.

faceoff_negative.comments: Hello! First of all thank you to Bzzagent and Mac for sending me this Glow Play Tendertalk lip balm in shade Banter! I was sent this item for free in exchange for my review, but that will not affect my rating in any way. To start off, I received a very nice color. The shade Banter is a playful red, and I found that, as someone who actually doesn't like a red lip on myself, I enjoyed this color a lot. It's definitely more of a bold red, however with how buildable it is, it can definitely be adjusted to your liking. I applied a few coats, and it was perfect, all I did was smudge it a bit to cover both of my lips. It doesn't apply like a lipstick at all, which I particularly enjoy. As someone with smaller lips, I'll often accidentally over-line my lips when using lipstick, but this didn't happen whatsoever with this product. I also found that this product was a bit difficult to work with, and one example would be something I tried out last night. I actually went to bed with some of the lip balm on, and when I woke up, it was still on my lips! And it didn't transfer whatsoever. I thought that was pretty nice, but at the same time, I can see how it could be annoying. Regardless, it came off easily with some micellar water. Besides the lip balm itself, I really liked the packaging! It's a smooth, sleek, reflective capsule, and very lightweight. I can definitely see myself carrying it around in my bag. The capsule itself also feels very well-constructed and fancy. I can't imagine it opening by accident or anything even when being jostled around in a bag as well. As for the price, although I didn't have to pay for it, I'm not sure I would pay full price for this product unless I found a shade that I really loved. Then, I would definitely consider. I think this would also work really beautifully with some lip liner, and I intend to use the product to the fullest, and I'll definitely be telling my friends and family about it. I think I know plenty of people who would love it.
faceoff_negative.headline: Max Glow Play Tendertalk Lip Balm
